<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-20 02:10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tokyo Stocks Close Higher  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    TOKYO (AP) -- The dollar edged lower against the yen Thursday afternoon
ahead of a weekend meeting of finance officials from advanced nations. Japanese
stocks closed higher.
</P>
<P>
	   The dollar bought 105.36 yen at midafternoon, down 0.16 yen from late
Wednesday, but unchanged from its late New York level of 105.36 yen overnight.
</P>
<P>
	   The benchmark 225-issue Nikkei Stock Average closed up 110.26 points, or
0.58 percent, to 19,008.01. On Wednesday, the average finished down 298.82
points, or 1.56 percent.
</P>
<P>
	   In currency dealings, the greenback moved in a narrow range in quiet trading
ahead of the meeting of Group of Seven finance ministers and central bank
governors in Tokyo on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
	   The dollar fell overnight to a low of 105.15 yen, but rebounded to 105.37
yen in early Asian trading on bids from some U.S. and Japanese investors ahead
of the G-7 meeting, traders said. Some investors expect the group to publicly
express concern about the strong yen.
</P>
<P>
	   Japanese officials have said the yen's rapid rise against the dollar will
hurt Japanese exports and profits, and thus adversely affect the nation's
economy which has begun to recover from a long slump.
</P>
<P>
	   In other currencies, the euro was traded at 106.60 yen, down from 107.06 yen
late Wednesday in Tokyo.
</P>
<P>
	   On the stock market, prices rose on buying of several blue chips as
investors were encouraged by a new record close on the technology-rich Nasdaq
Composite Index in New York overnight.
</P>
<P>
	   The market was being led by strong gains in several blue-chip stocks, with
Sony, Toyota Motor and Matsushita Electric Industrial all posting rises
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
	   The Nasdaq index ended Wednesday at 4,151.27, its first closing record high
since Jan. 3. The Dow Jones industrial average, however, fell 71.36 points, or
0.6 percent, to close at 11,489.36.
</P>
<P>
	   The broader Tokyo Stock Price Index of all issues listed on the first
section was up 1.83 points, or 0.11 percent, to 1,633.11. The TOPIX closed down
34.56 points, or 2.07 percent, the day before.
</P>
<P>
	   The yield on the benchmark 10-year Japanese government bond rose to 1.7900
percent from Wednesday's finish of 1.7550 percent. Its price fell 0.30 point to
100.08.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
