<HEADLINE> David Letterman Leaves Hospital  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    NEW YORK (AP) -- There was no top 10, but David Letterman was still cracking
jokes as he left the hospital five days after quintuple bypass heart surgery.
</P>
<P>
	   "I think there must have been some kind of mixup. I went to the hospital to
get a face-lift," Letterman said Wednesday as he left the hospital, according to
spokesman Howard Rubenstein.
</P>
<P>
	   Letterman, 52, was continuing to recuperate at an undisclosed location,
Rubenstein said.
</P>
<P>
	   Letterman had the emergency surgery at New York-Presbyterian Hospital on
Friday after tests showed that one of his arteries was clogged.
</P>
<P>
	   Rubenstein said he did not know when Letterman would be able to return to
the "Late Show." CBS is airing reruns while Letterman recovers.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
