<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beatty To Receive Honorary Award  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    BEVERLY HILLS, Calif. (AP) -- Warren Beatty will receive the Irving G.
Thalberg Award at this year's Oscars ceremony, an honor given to producers whose
work reflects a "consistently high quality."
</P>
<P>
	   Beatty is the only filmmaker nominated for Oscars in acting, writing,
directing and producing for a single movie.
</P>
<P>
	   Academy president Robert Rehme noted Wednesday that Beatty was twice
nominated in all four categories, for "Heaven Can Wait" in 1978 and "Reds" in
1981.
</P>
<P>
	   Orson Welles was nominated for acting, writing and directing on "Citizen
Kane," but the film's best-picture nomination was credited to the production
company under what were then the Academy's rules in 1941.
</P>
<P>
	   The 72nd annual Oscars are scheduled for March 26. The Thalberg award is
named after the legendary MGM movie mogul.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
