<HEADLINE> Dow Climbs 63; Nasdaq Rises 54  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is up 63 points in today's
early going. Advancing issues and decliners are evenly split on the New York
Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
	   The Nasdaq Composite Index is ahead 54 points and the Standard &AMP; Poor's 500
Stock Index is up five points.
</P>
<P>
	   Better-than-expected reports from a host of companies are putting investors
in a good mood.
</P>
<P>
	   GM, General Electric, IBM, Apple and America Online are among the companies
topping analysts' estimates with their quarterly figures.
</P>
<P>
	   At the same time, bond market interest rates are moving higher, and some
analysts say that could keep any gains in check.
</P>
</TEXT>
