<HEADLINE> Dallas Armored Truck Heists Probed  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DALLAS (AP) -- In the area's third armored truck heist in two weeks, a robber
wielding a gun and pepper spray escaped with thousands of dollars.
</P>
<P>
	   Police said a man overpowered an Armored Transport truck guard at a downtown
bus station in Dallas on Wednesday and got away with about $28,000 in cash.
</P>
<P>
	   On Tuesday, another Armored Transport guard was attacked as he left a
clothing store in Arlington, and last week a Loomis Fargo armored truck was
robbed at a Home Depot store in Fort Worth.
</P>
<P>
	   No arrests have been made, FBI spokeswoman Marjorie Poche said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
	   Officials with Los Angeles-based Armored Transport Inc. referred questions
to the FBI. The company offers armored truck services in 17 states and the
District of Columbia.
</P>
<P>
	   Dallas-Fort Worth had nine armored truck robberies last year. Six arrests
were made in those cases, according to the FBI.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
