<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-20 22:51 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Village Voice Gets New Publisher  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Judy Miszner was named publisher of the Village Voice on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
	   She replaces David Schneiderman, who is the new chief executive officer of
Village Voice Media. The company consists of the Voice -- a 250,000 circulation
weekly founded in 1955 -- and six other weekly alternative newspapers.
</P>
<P>
	   George Troyano, the vice president of sales, will succeed Miszner, who had
been been vice president of sales and marketing for more than a year.
</P>
<P>
	   The money management firm of Weiss, Peck &AMP; Greer was the leading partner in
an investment group that bought the Voice and its associated newspapers recently
from Stern Publishing.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-01-20-00 2251 </TRAILER>
