<HEADLINE> Military Plane Crashes, Pilot Dies  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOISE, Idaho (AP) -- A military attack jet crashed Thursday night in
southwestern Idaho, killing an Idaho National Guard pilot.
</P>
<P>
	   Ada County sheriff's dispatch supervisor Myrna Harris said the pilot was the
only person aboard the A-10 when it went down in a field near Star, about 15
miles northwest of Boise, at 6:42 p.m. MST.
</P>
<P>
	   Harris said investigators with the Federal Aviation Administration were
examining the crash site Thursday night, but had not determined why the plane
went down.
</P>
<P>
	   An eyewitness said the plane seemed to arc before plummeting.
</P>
<P>
	   The attack jet was believed to be from the Idaho National Guard facility at
Boise. The National Guard shares an air field with Boise's city airport.
</P>
</TEXT>
