<HEADLINE> Louisville 72, No. 23 DePaul 59  </HEADLINE>
    By STEVE BAILEY AP Sports Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
	   LOUISVILLE, Ky. (AP) -- Tony Williams scored 18 points and Louisville beat
No. 23 DePaul 72-59 Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
	   Marques Maybin, who missed Louisville's last game because of illness, had 17
and Reece Gaines 11. The Cardinals (11-5, 3-2 Conference USA) ended a two-game
losing streak.
</P>
<P>
	   The victory was Louisville's third against a ranked opponent at home this
season. The Cardinals, unbeaten at Freedom Hall, beat then-No. 6 North Carolina
97-80 and then-No. 18 Utah 77-55.
</P>
<P>
	   Bobby Simmons led DePaul (12-5, 3-2) with 18 points. Quentin Richardson, who
came into the game averaging 19.4 points, was held to only 12 on 5-of-14
shooting.
</P>
<P>
	   Louisville opened the second half with a 13-2 run to take a 47-32 lead. An
11-2 DePaul run closed the gap to 51-46 with 8:30 to play, but the Blue Demons
got no closer.
</P>
<P>
	   Louisville shot 57 percent (25-of-44) from the floor while the Blue Demons
shot only 41 percent (22-of-54)
</P>
<P>
	   The Cardinals, who were only 5-of-31 on 3-pointers in consecutive losses at
UAB and Marquette, were 9-of-15 against the Blue Demons. DePaul, which came into
the game hitting 37 percent of its 3-pointers, finished only 3-of-14.
</P>
<P>
	   Trailing 19-15, Quintin Bailey scored seven points during a 13-2 run as
Louisville took a 28-21 lead with 4:14 to play in the first half.
</P>
<P>
	   The Cardinals led 34-30 at halftime, holding Richardson to only two points
and five shot attempts.
</P>
